page.title: 11Shobrooke Park Trees.
page.content: Alleys of trees in Shobrooke Park Eaten leaves and worn away bark Some growing nut and some just plain seeds Hundreds of colours and lots of breeds. When we went to Shobrooke Park there were 5 different kinds of tree that we identified which were Lime, Oak, Horse-Chestnut, Ash and Copper Beech. When we first came in to Shobrooke Park there were a few Oak, a few Ash, a few Horse Chestnut and a few Lime. Then we went through a kissing gate and there was an avenue of lime trees, and at the end of the avenue there was a Copper Beech.
